#originalTopic=Debate:_Single-payer_universal_health_care
 Many businesses cannot pay the private health insurance of employees (Indeed, the Big Three of U.S. car manufacturers cite health-care provision as a reason for their ongoing financial travails. The cost of health insurance to U.S. car manufacturers adds between USD 900 and USD 1,400 to each car made in the U.S.A.).
